{
  "text": "My understanding of an educator’s role has also changed. I once believed that teachers and Education Assistants were mainly responsible for teaching knowledge, maintaining discipline, and helping students achieve good grades.\n\nI now understand that educators also support development by creating safe environments, building trusting relationships, modelling skills, and providing opportunities to practise. In my work as an EA, I may use a visual schedule, divide a task into smaller steps, repeat an instruction, or provide additional time. My goal will be to offer enough support for the student to succeed while still encouraging independence.",
  "voice": "en-GB-SoniaNeural",
